## üìÇ Project Structure

```
glc/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ glc/             # Source code
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ lexer.py     # Tokenizer
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ parser.py    # Parser ‚Üí AST
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ t2c.py       # AST ‚Üí C transpiler
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ main.py      # CLI entry point
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ examples/        # Example GoatLang programs
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ pyproject.toml   # Build config
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ README.md
```

---

## ‚ö° How It Works

1. **Lexing** ‚Äì source code ‚Üí tokens
2. **Parsing** ‚Äì tokens ‚Üí AST (abstract syntax tree)
3. **Transpiling** ‚Äì AST ‚Üí C code
4. **Compiling** ‚Äì C ‚Üí native executable (via GCC/clang)
5. **Running** ‚Äì GLC runs the binary automatically

---

## üõ† Requirements

* Python ‚â• 3.8
* GCC or Clang (for compiling generated C code)

---

## üöß Limitations

* No user-defined functions yet (only `fn main`)
* String concatenation is still basic (uses buffers + `strcpy/strcat`)
* Error messages are primitive
* No standard library (beyond `print`)

